laboratory_examinations.findings: Liver shows small hypodensities within the right and left lobes, too small to characterize; otherwise normal. No free air or free fluid present. The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled measuring up to 1.2 cm in diameter, consistent with appendicitis. No perforation or abscess formation. There is a left-sided adnexal cyst measuring 2.3 x 2.3 cm.
